  "title": "Braveheart | Great Movie But How True Was the Story?",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 3378.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 6297.0,
      "end_time": 9216.0,
      "text": "In 1995, Mel Gibson and Icon Productions"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 9217.0,
      "end_time": 12303.0,
      "text": "released Braveheart, which was nominated for 61 awards"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 12303.0,
      "end_time": 15390.0,
      "text": "and won 31 of those, including Oscars for Best Picture"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 15390.0,
      "end_time": 16516.0,
      "text": "and Best Director."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 16516.0,
      "end_time": 18810.0,
      "text": "If there had been an award for least historically"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18810.0,
      "end_time": 21145.0,
      "text": "accurate movie, it would have won that as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21146.0,
      "end_time": 23273.0,
      "text": "The timeline is wrong, the events they got right"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23273.0,
      "end_time": 26151.0,
      "text": "are depicted wrong, the look of it is laughably wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 26151.0,
      "end_time": 27610.0,
      "text": "and there are some artistic choices"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 27610.0,
      "end_time": 29863.0,
      "text": "they made regarding the characters that are wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 29863.0,
      "end_time": 32281.0,
      "text": "In 1276, when the story began, the film"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 32281.0,
      "end_time": 34324.0,
      "text": "shows Scotland struggling to determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 34325.0,
      "end_time": 36578.0,
      "text": "who would be the king after the deaths of Alexander"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 36578.0,
      "end_time": 38329.0,
      "text": "III and his three children."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 38329.0,
      "end_time": 42125.0,
      "text": "The thing is, all four people were actually alive and 1276."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 42125.0,
      "end_time": 45170.0,
      "text": "In fact, the king wouldn&#39;t die for another 10 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 45170.0,
      "end_time": 47714.0,
      "text": "In 1286, the rebellion started, but it"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 47714.0,
      "end_time": 50700.0,
      "text": "didn&#39;t start the way the movie would have us believe."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 50800.0,
      "end_time": 52469.0,
      "text": "In the film, William Wallace&#39;s father Malcolm"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 52469.0,
      "end_time": 55805.0,
      "text": "was among those Scots lured to a fake Scottish summit only"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 55805.0,
      "end_time": 57223.0,
      "text": "to be attacked by the British."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 57223.0,
      "end_time": 60393.0,
      "text": "Malcolm&#39;s death was the first spark of young William&#39;s hatred"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 60393.0,
      "end_time": 60977.0,
      "text": "for England."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 60977.0,
      "end_time": 63200.0,
      "text": "But in reality, there was no summit."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 63210.0,
      "end_time": 65815.0,
      "text": "That inciting incident in the life of the protagonist"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 65815.0,
      "end_time": 67442.0,
      "text": "was a total fabrication."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 67442.0,
      "end_time": 69943.0,
      "text": "In 1297, the Scottish fought the British"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 69944.0,
      "end_time": 71571.0,
      "text": "in the Battle of Stirling Bridge."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 71571.0,
      "end_time": 73530.0,
      "text": "That made its way into the film, but why"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 73531.0,
      "end_time": 76326.0,
      "text": "did they show the battle without including the titular bridge?"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 76326.0,
      "end_time": 78244.0,
      "text": "The real life bridge created a bottleneck"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 78244.0,
      "end_time": 80330.0,
      "text": "that was essential to the Scots&#39; strategy."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 80330.0,
      "end_time": 83416.0,
      "text": "Also in 1297, Wallace&#39;s men raided several cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 83416.0,
      "end_time": 85835.0,
      "text": "in Northumberland, which is in the northeast of England."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 85835.0,
      "end_time": 87836.0,
      "text": "The film showed the Scots sacking York,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 87837.0,
      "end_time": 89631.0,
      "text": "which is over 100 miles south."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 89631.0,
      "end_time": 92342.0,
      "text": "In 1298, the Battle of Falkirk took place."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 92342.0,
      "end_time": 94344.0,
      "text": "During the film version, Irish soldiers"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 94344.0,
      "end_time": 96950.0,
      "text": "were inspired by Wallace and his men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 96950.0,
      "end_time": 98140.0,
      "text": "so they abandoned their post with the British"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 98140.0,
      "end_time": 99307.0,
      "text": "and joined the Scots."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 99307.0,
      "end_time": 101476.0,
      "text": "The real battle didn&#39;t include any Irish."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 101476.0,
      "end_time": 103311.0,
      "text": "Now, let&#39;s take a look at the costuming."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 103311.0,
      "end_time": 105688.0,
      "text": "In the 1300s, kilts weren&#39;t a thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 105688.0,
      "end_time": 108566.0,
      "text": "Those didn&#39;t come into fashion until around the 1600s."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 108566.0,
      "end_time": 111690.0,
      "text": "The men would have been dressed in tunics and hosen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 111690.0,
      "end_time": 113321.0,
      "text": "maybe even baggy shorts called braies."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 113321.0,
      "end_time": 114989.0,
      "text": "Scottish males at the time wouldn&#39;t"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 114989.0,
      "end_time": 116533.0,
      "text": "have had long hair, since that would"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 116533.0,
      "end_time": 117826.0,
      "text": "have been considered feminine."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 117826.0,
      "end_time": 120244.0,
      "text": "And if they had, they certainly wouldn&#39;t have spruced it up"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 120245.0,
      "end_time": 122330.0,
      "text": "with pretty braids and adornments."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 122330.0,
      "end_time": 124249.0,
      "text": "Now, let&#39;s address the blue face paint."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 124249.0,
      "end_time": 125958.0,
      "text": "In the fourth century, one could find"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 125959.0,
      "end_time": 128169.0,
      "text": "a warrior sporting such paint, or more likely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 128169.00000000001,
      "end_time": 129671.00000000001,
      "text": "tattoos on the battlefield."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 129669.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131631.0,
      "text": "Those warriors were Picts, the people"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 131631.0,
      "end_time": 133925.0,
      "text": "indigenous to the British Isles over 1,000 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 133925.0,
      "end_time": 136636.0,
      "text": "before the events of Braveheart took place."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 136636.0,
      "end_time": 140682.0,
      "text": "In the mid-1700s, bagpipes were banned as an instrument of war."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 140682.0,
      "end_time": 142433.0,
      "text": "That didn&#39;t stop the movie from talking"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 142433.0,
      "end_time": 146311.0,
      "text": "about bagpipes being illegal some 400 years before the ban."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 146312.0,
      "end_time": 148606.0,
      "text": "At least the errors found on the Scottish soldiers"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 148606.0,
      "end_time": 150233.0,
      "text": "were matched by the British soldiers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 150233.0,
      "end_time": 151901.0,
      "text": "who were wearing matching uniforms that"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 151901.0,
      "end_time": 153236.0,
      "text": "didn&#39;t exist at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 153236.0,
      "end_time": 156530.0,
      "text": "What also didn&#39;t exist at the time was a pagan British king."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 156531.0,
      "end_time": 158658.0,
      "text": "Edward I was very much a Christian"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 158658.0,
      "end_time": 160785.0,
      "text": "who even participated in the Crusades."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 160785.0,
      "end_time": 163288.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s look at the film&#39;s depiction of Edward II"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 163288.0,
      "end_time": 164455.0,
      "text": "homosexuality."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 164455.0,
      "end_time": 167625.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s unclear whether he had sexual relationships with men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 167625.0,
      "end_time": 170860.0,
      "text": "and we don&#39;t know if his father knew or cared about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 170860.0,
      "end_time": 172255.0,
      "text": "But the fact is he was married."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 172255.0,
      "end_time": 174465.0,
      "text": "He and his wife had tension, but that didn&#39;t stem"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 174465.0,
      "end_time": 176175.0,
      "text": "from him finding her repulsive."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 176175.0,
      "end_time": 177468.0,
      "text": "He had four kids with her."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 177468.0,
      "end_time": 180471.0,
      "text": "Other than Isabella, the person most associated with Edward"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 180471.0,
      "end_time": 182849.0,
      "text": "was Piers Gaveston, whom the movie shows"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 182849.0,
      "end_time": 184767.0,
      "text": "being thrown out of the window to his death"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 184767.0,
      "end_time": 185894.0,
      "text": "by Edward&#39;s father."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 185894.0,
      "end_time": 187395.0,
      "text": "That simply didn&#39;t happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 187395.0,
      "end_time": 190899.0,
      "text": "William Wallace never seduced Edward&#39;s wife Isabella."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 190899.0,
      "end_time": 193610.0,
      "text": "She never met him and was only 13 when he died."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 193610.0,
      "end_time": 196863.0,
      "text": "Isabella and Edward didn&#39;t marry until several years after that."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 196863.0,
      "end_time": 199157.0,
      "text": "And for the biggest fact bending of all--"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 199157.0,
      "end_time": 202760.0,
      "text": "William Wallace wasn&#39;t referred to as \"Braveheart.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 202760.0,
      "end_time": 205914.0,
      "text": "In 1329, that honor was bestowed upon Robert the Bruce, whom"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 205914.0,
      "end_time": 208541.0,
      "text": "the movie erroneously suggested was involved in Wallace&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 208541.0,
      "end_time": 209959.0,
      "text": "capture and execution."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 209959.0,
      "end_time": 212545.0,
      "text": "He was called Braveheart because, as per his wishes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 212545.0,
      "end_time": 214297.0,
      "text": "his heart was posthumously removed"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 214297.0,
      "end_time": 216549.0,
      "text": "so it can be taken on a crusade before being"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 216549.0,
      "end_time": 217842.0,
      "text": "buried in Scotland."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 217842.0,
      "end_time": 220940.0,
      "text": "What else did they get wrong about William Wallace?"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 220940.0,
      "end_time": 223430.0,
      "text": "His dad was probably Alex Wallace, not Malcolm Wallace."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 223431.0,
      "end_time": 225892.0,
      "text": "Regardless, neither died when William was young,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 225892.0,
      "end_time": 228519.0,
      "text": "and they were both minor nobility rather than commoners,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 228519.0,
      "end_time": 229896.0,
      "text": "as portrayed in the movie."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 229896.0,
      "end_time": 231814.0,
      "text": "Since William wasn&#39;t orphaned as a child,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 231814.0,
      "end_time": 234317.0,
      "text": "he didn&#39;t have to go live with his uncle Argyle, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 234317.0,
      "end_time": 237612.0,
      "text": "is just as well, because Uncle Argyle didn&#39;t exist."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 237612.0,
      "end_time": 240698.0,
      "text": "William&#39;s wife Murron, existed, except her name was Marion."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 240698.0,
      "end_time": 242784.0,
      "text": "That fudging makes sense because Murron is"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 242784.0,
      "end_time": 244327.0,
      "text": "the Gaelic version of the name."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 244327.0,
      "end_time": 246204.0,
      "text": "And yes, she was killed by the British,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 246204.0,
      "end_time": 248373.0,
      "text": "but it wasn&#39;t after an assault by a British soldier."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 248373.0,
      "end_time": 251840.0,
      "text": "It was because she housed her fugitive husband after he"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 251840.0,
      "end_time": 252835.0,
      "text": "ran from a marketplace brawl."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 252835.0,
      "end_time": 255838.0,
      "text": "William was also killed by the British in 1305,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 255838.0,
      "end_time": 258257.0,
      "text": "and this is one example where the movie actually toned it"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 258257.0,
      "end_time": 259425.0,
      "text": "down for some reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 259425.0,
      "end_time": 261803.0,
      "text": "He wasn&#39;t just hanged, disemboweled, drawn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 261803.0,
      "end_time": 262637.0,
      "text": "and quartered."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 262637.0,
      "end_time": 264847.0,
      "text": "He was also dragged naked through the streets for six"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 264847.0,
      "end_time": 267140.0,
      "text": "miles, fully emasculated, forced to watch"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 267141.0,
      "end_time": 268601.0,
      "text": "while his intestines were burned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 268601.0,
      "end_time": 270395.0,
      "text": "and then his heart and head were removed."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 270395.0,
      "end_time": 272229.0,
      "text": "His head was displayed on London Bridge"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 272230.0,
      "end_time": 275240.0,
      "text": "while his other parts were displayed all over London."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 275240.0,
      "end_time": 278194.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the real story of William Wallace."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 278194.0,
      "end_time": 280196.0,
      "text": "If you like what you see, be sure to subscribe"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 280196.0,
      "end_time": 282573.0,
      "text": "to the Weird History Channel, and watch our other videos."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
